<section class="inner-sec">
  <div class="sec-eyebrow">How it works in a practice</div>
  <h2>Every inquiry answered, every patient routed</h2>
  <p class="lede">One receptionist covers the phone, the texts, the website, and the socials — and its whole job is getting the right patient onto your schedule while your team focuses on care.</p>
  <div class="svc-grid">
    <div class="svc"><strong>Missed-call text-back</strong>A call you can't take instantly becomes a text: "Sorry we missed you — want to get you scheduled?"</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Answers the front-desk questions</strong>Hours, location, what you treat, new-patient availability, how to book — answered instantly and accurately, any hour.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Books straight to your calendar</strong>New patients get sent to your real booking page for a consult or appointment — no phone tag, no double-booking.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Text &amp; social messages</strong>Website chat, texts, and Facebook and Instagram DMs answered in minutes with real info and a booking link.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>New-patient follow-up</strong>Inquiries that don't book right away get a gentle, automatic nudge so they don't slip through the cracks.</div>
    <div class="svc"><strong>Human handoff</strong>Anything clinical or sensitive is flagged to your staff with a summary — the AI never gives medical advice or handles records.</div>
  </div>
</section>

